---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About ASCIIMoon | Moon Phase Tracker"
  description="ASCIIMoon tracks the moon's phases and uses ASCII art to create a basic visual representation of the moon's current appearance based on light percentage."
  keywords="moon phases, ASCII moon, moon tracker, moon phase tracker, ASCII art, lunar phases, moon calendar, moon cycle, moon phase app, phase of the moon"
  canonicalURL="https://asciimoon.com/about"
  robots="index, follow"
>
  <main>
    <section>
      <h1>About ASCIIMoon</h1>
      <p>
        ASCIIMoon is a small web app that tracks the moon's phases and uses <a
          href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASCII_art"
          rel="nofollower noopener"
          target="_blank">ASCII art</a
        > to create a basic visual representation of the moon's current appearance
        based on light percentage.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is a personal project, and is in no way a precise representation.
      </p>
      <!-- BUY ME A COFFEE LINK -->
      <p>
        Find this website helpful or fun? <br /><a
          href="https://www.buymeacoffee.com/seanrooney"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer noopener">☕️ Buy me a coffee</a
        >
      </p>
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
      <h2 id="repo">Repo/Source Code</h2>
      <p>Here is the link to the GitHub repository and source code:</p>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/Sean-93/asciimoon"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer noopener">github.com/Sean-93/asciimoon</a
      >
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
      <h2 id="repo">SunCalc Library for Moon Phase Calculations</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses the SunCalc library via a CDN to track the moonlight
        percentage.<a
          href="https://suncalc.net/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer noopener">suncalc.net</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
      <h2>Photo of the Moon is from NASA's Archive</h2>

      <p>
        The photo of the Moon used on this site is from NASA's archive: <a
          href="https://images.nasa.gov/details-PIA00405"
          rel="noreferrer noopener"
          target="_blank">images.nasa.gov/details-PIA00405</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        It was taken on December 7, 1992 by the <a
          href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galileo_(spacecraft)"
          rel="noreferrer noopener"
          target="_blank">Galileo</a
        > on its way towards the Jupiter system.
      </p>
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
      <h2>ASCII Art Generated by Manytools.org</h2>
      <p>
        Ascii art from the moon photo was generated thanks to <a
          href="https://manytools.org/hacker-tools/convert-images-to-ascii-art/"
          rel="noreferrer nofollow"
          target="_blank"
          >manytools.org/hacker-tools/convert-images-to-ascii-art</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
      <h2>Website Built with Astro</h2>
      <p>
        This website was built using the Astro web framework. Get started
        buildng with Astro today at <a
          href="https://astro.build/"
          rel="noreferrer nofollow"
          target="_blank">astro.build</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
        <hr />
    <section>
      <h2>Follow on Neocities</h2>
      <p>
        Follow this website's profile on Neocities <a
          href="https://neocities.org/site/asciimoon"
          rel="noreferrer nofollow"
          target="_blank">neocities.org/site/asciimoon</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

